Turkey Equity Movers: Arcelik, Bank Asya, Garanti, Yapi Kredi

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-08-03T15:36:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/arcelik-bank-asya-garanti-yapi-kredi-turkey-equity-preview.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell for a fourth day, losing 443.53, or 0.7 percent, to
61,315.08 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Arcelik AS (ARCLK)  , Turkey’s largest household
appliances maker, dropped 22 kurus, or 2.9 percent, to 7.26
liras, its lowest since March 31. The company reported that
second-quarter earnings fell to 137.2 million liras ($80
million), down from 160.8 million liras last year.  Asya Katilim Bankasi (ASYAB TI), an Islamic bank, rose 7
kurus, or 3 percent, to 2.42 liras, the biggest gain since May
31. The company had second-quarter profit of 55.5 million liras,
it said in a statement to the exchange after the close
yesterday.  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN)  , Turkey’s largest
listed bank, gained 12 kurus, or 1.6 percent, to 7.52 liras, its
highest since July 8. Second-quarter earnings rose to 943.2
million liras, exceeding estimates, it said in a statement to
the exchange today.  Yapi & Kredi Bankasi AS (YKBNK TI), the bank part-owned by
UniCredit SpA, added 5 kurus, or 1.2 percent, to 4.08 liras
after reporting profit that topped estimates. Second-quarter
profit fell to 441.8 million liras, compared with 436.4 million
liras, according to the average of 12 analyst estimates compiled
by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
